            <name>Debian Updates check</name>
            <description>Template for Zabbix to check if in Debian based OS updates are available.

Add user parameters to Agent config is required.

UserParameter=debian_updates.package,apt-get update &gt; /dev/null 2&gt;&amp;1 &amp;&amp; apt-get upgrade -s | grep -c ^Inst
UserParameter=debian_updates.security,apt-get update &gt; /dev/null 2&gt;&amp;1 &amp;&amp; apt-get upgrade -s | grep ^Inst | grep -c security</description>
            <groups>
                <group>
                    <name>Templates/Operating systems</name>
                </group>
            </groups>
            <items>
                <item>
                    <uuid>150486066b2043e38ee763cd59755db6</uuid>
                    <name>Updates available</name>
